{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nDeferred from b550. gerrit-verify.yaml's monolithic build-and-test job HAND-COPIES the gate+suite command set that test.yml runs across its lint + pip-audit + test jobs. tests/unit/test_ci_workflow_parity.py polices that copy against drift. Factor the shared gate+suite into ONE reusable workflow_call file (the pattern _optionality.yml already proves) so drift is impossible by construction, and the copy-sync guard can be replaced by a delegation guard.\n\n## What\nAdd .github/workflows/_build-and-test.yml — a reusable (workflow_call) workflow, checkout parameterized by gerrit-refspec/gerrit-project/gerrit-url EXACTLY like _optionality.yml (branch-head via actions/checkout when gerrit-refspec=='' ; checkout-gerrit-change-action on the patchset when set), taking NO secrets. It defines THREE jobs mirroring test.yml's current decomposition (so test.yml keeps its job-graph parallelism):\n- lint: make lint + pre-commit (SKIP no-commit-to-branch,lint,typecheck) + make typecheck + make config-check.\n- pip-audit: the network-retried dependency-vuln scan (one ubuntu job).\n- test: the os×py matrix (install .[dev] + git identity + Module-size + Prompt-index + Env-var + Docs-index + README-quickstart + CLI-ref + MCP-ref + Security-pin + Criteria-routing + server.json + Public-types gates + default suite + integration tier).\nThe union of these three == gerrit-verify.yaml's current build-and-test gate set, so nothing is dropped.\n\nRewire callers:\n- test.yml: delete its inline lint/pip-audit/test jobs; call the reusable with NO inputs (branch-head). Keep golden-path, artifact-probe, and the secret-scoped external job (which the reusable, taking no secrets, must not absorb).\n- gerrit-verify.yaml: replace the monolithic build-and-test job with a single reusable-call job STILL NAMED build-and-test (needs: [clear-vote, require-ticket]); this also splits gerrit's currently-inline lint/mypy/config-check/pre-commit out of the 4x matrix so they run once (a net improvement). clear-vote, require-ticket, optionality, golden-path, verify-identity, and vote are unchanged; vote still lists 'build-and-test, optionality' in needs, and im-open/workflow-conclusion still folds the reusable's job conclusions into the Verified vote (already proven for optionality).\n\ngolden-path remains duplicated between the two files for now (out of scope; smaller duplication, larger blast radius — noted as a follow-up).\n\n## Correct premise: test_ci_workflow_parity.py enforces FIVE functions, not one\nIt is NOT 'solely a copy-sync policer'. Three of its five functions enforce independent safety invariants that MUST be preserved (relocated to scan the reusable), not dropped:\n1. test_verified_gate_runs_every_shared_gate — the copy-sync check. REWRITE: assert each _SHARED_GATE_SIGNATURES value appears in _build-and-test.yml (the reusable), AND that BOTH test.yml and gerrit-verify.yaml contain the delegation string './.github/workflows/_build-and-test.yml'. (gate exists + both lanes run it via one source.)\n2. test_no_drift_script_gate_is_verified_only_in_branch_ci — REWRITE: scan _build-and-test.yml for scripts/*.py (they now gate both lanes by construction); _INTENTIONAL_SCRIPT_ASYMMETRIES stays empty. The old test.yml-minus-gerrit diff is obsolete under a single source.\n3. test_optionality_contract_gates_the_verified_path — SURVIVES UNCHANGED (independent invariant: optionality reusable wiring + GERRIT_REFSPEC + vote-needs-optionality). Not touched by this change.\n4. test_branch_sensitive_precommit_hooks_skipped_in_ci — SURVIVES; retarget _precommit_all_files_steps at _build-and-test.yml (the reusable now owns the single pre-commit step) and assert no-commit-to-branch is in its SKIP.\n5. test_ci_redundant_hooks_skipped_in_precommit — SURVIVES; same retarget: assert lint+typecheck are SKIPped in the reusable's pre-commit step AND that the direct 'make lint'/'make typecheck' steps still exist in the reusable (linter runs exactly once).\nAlso update tests/unit/test_workflow_names.py: add '_build-and-test.yml' -> 'Build and Test (reusable)' to the locked naming table so the naming gate covers it.\n\n## Validation note\ng2p dispatches gerrit-verify.yaml from main's ref, so THIS change's own Verified run uses the OLD inline gate; the refactored reusable path first runs post-merge via test.yml (branch-head), watched immediately after landing. actionlint (make lint) validates the reusable 'uses:' wiring + workflow_call input schema locally pre-merge; the rewritten parity + naming tests validate the structure.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] .github/workflows/_build-and-test.yml exists as a workflow_call reusable with lint + pip-audit + test(matrix) jobs, checkout parameterized by gerrit-refspec, taking no secrets.\n- [ ] test.yml and gerrit-verify.yaml BOTH delegate to ./.github/workflows/_build-and-test.yml; gerrit-verify's reusable-call job is named build-and-test and vote still needs it; the Verified vote still works end-to-end (confirmed by the first post-merge run + the next change's Verified +1).\n- [ ] All five test_ci_workflow_parity.py functions are updated per the enumeration above (three safety invariants preserved, retargeted to the reusable; two copy-sync checks rewritten as delegation+reusable-content checks); no safety guard silently dropped.\n- [ ] test_workflow_names.py covers _build-and-test.yml.\n- [ ] make lint (actionlint over all workflows) + the workflow tests pass; lands through Gerrit with LLM-Review +1 and Verified +1."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784445566602941001,"uuid":"24aafffe-e4b3-47a8-90d5-b41188719b12"}